%matplotlib inline
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.datasets import make_blobs
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import axes3d
from rerf.urerf import UnsupervisedRandomForest
from sklearn.cluster import AgglomerativeClustering
from sklearn.cluster import SpectralClustering
from sklearn.metrics import adjusted_rand_score

centers_2D=[(30,1.5),(0,0),(-25,1)]
X_2D, true_label_2D = make_blobs(n_samples=500, 
                                 n_features=2,
                                 centers=4, 
                                 cluster_std=.5,
                                 shuffle=True, 
                                 random_state=0)

X_2D_NoNoise=X_2D
X_2D_HighNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, 15, size=X_2D.shape)
X_2D_MediumNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, 3, size=X_2D.shape)
X_2D_LowNoise=X_2D+np.random.normal(0, .5, size=X_2D.shape)

centers_3D=[(30,1.5,1),(0,0,0),(-25,1,2)]
X_3D, true_label_3D = make_blobs(n_samples=500, 
                                 n_features=3,
                                 centers=centers_3D, 
                                 cluster_std=0.5,
                                 shuffle=True, 
                                 random_state=0)
X_3D_NoNoise=X_3D
X_3D_HighNoise=X_3D+np.random.normal(0, 15, size=X_3D.shape)
X_3D_MediumNoise=X_3D+np.random.normal(0, 3, size=X_3D.shape)
X_3D_LowNoise=X_3D+np.random.normal(0, .5, size=X_3D.shape)

#plotting 2D data
def PlotTrue2D(x,y,z,X_2D,true_label,title):
    plt.subplot(x,y,z)
    sns.scatterplot(X_2D[:,0],X_2D[:,1],hue=true_label,edgecolor='black');
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.title(title)
    
f, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 15), sharex=True)
f.suptitle('Plotting the True Labels for 2D Data')
PlotTrue2D(2,2,1,X_2D_NoNoise,true_label_2D,'No Noise')
PlotTrue2D(2,2,2,X_2D_HighNoise,true_label_2D,'High Noise')
PlotTrue2D(2,2,3,X_2D_MediumNoise,true_label_2D,'Medium Noise')
PlotTrue2D(2,2,4,X_2D_LowNoise,true_label_2D,'Low Noise')

# plotting 3D data
def PlotTrueLabels(x,y,z,X_3D,true_label,title):
    plt.subplot(x,y,z)
    ax = plt.axes(projection='3d')
    colors = ['g','b','r']
    for i, col in zip(X_3D,true_label):
        ax.scatter3D(i[0],i[1],i[2], color = colors[col],edgecolor='black')
    plt.title('True labels for 3D data')
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y')
    ax.set_zlabel('Z')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
f, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(7, 7), sharex=True)
f.suptitle('Plotting the True Labels for 3D Data')
PlotTrueLabels(2,2,1,X_3D_NoNoise,true_label_3D,'No Noise')
PlotTrueLabels(2,2,2,X_3D_HighNoise,true_label_3D,'High Noise')
PlotTrueLabels(2,2,3,X_3D_MediumNoise,true_label_3D,'Medium Noise')
PlotTrueLabels(2,2,4,X_3D_LowNoise,true_label_3D,'Low Noise')

%timeit
def spectral_clustering(sd,features,centers):
    I = []
    cluster=[]
    Rand_Index=[]
    
    for i in range (0,30):
        I.append(i+1)
    A_Spectral = []
    cluster_A = []

    
    X, true_label = make_blobs(n_samples=200, 
                                 n_features=features,
                                 centers=centers, 
                                 cluster_std=0.5,
                                 shuffle=True, 
                                 random_state=0)
        
    X_Noise=X+np.random.normal(0, sd, size=X.shape)
    clf = UnsupervisedRandomForest(projection_matrix="RerF", random_state=0)
    clf.fit(X_Noise)
    sim_mat = clf.transform()
    inp=symmetrize(sim_mat)
        
      
    for j in range(0,25):    
        cluster_A.append([])
        A_Spectral.append([])
        
        for i in range (0,30):
            cluster_A[j].append(SpectralClustering(n_clusters=i+1, affinity="precomputed",random_state=None))
            predict_labels_A = cluster_A[j][i].fit_predict(inp)
            A_Spectral[j].append(adjusted_rand_score(true_label, predict_labels_A))
            Rand_Index.append(A_Spectral[j][i])
            cluster.append(I[i])
    
    return Rand_Index,cluster

# finding rand index for 2D data 

Rand_Index_2D_Spectral,cluster_Spectral=spectral_clustering(0,2,centers_2D)
Rand_Index_2D_HighNoise_Spectral,cluster_HighNoise_Spectral=spectral_clustering(15,2,centers_2D)
Rand_Index_2D_MediumNoise_Spectral,cluster_MediumNoise_Spectral=spectral_clustering(3,2,centers_2D)
Rand_Index_2D_LowNoise_Spectral,cluster_LowNoise_Spectral=spectral_clustering(.5,2,centers_2D)  

# finding rand index for 3D data

Rand_Index_3D_Spectral,cluster_Spectral=spectral_clustering(0,3,centers_3D)
Rand_Index_3D_HighNoise_Spectral,cluster_HighNoise_Spectral=spectral_clustering(15,3,centers_3D)
Rand_Index_3D_MediumNoise_Spectral,cluster_MediumNoise_Spectral=spectral_clustering(3,3,centers_3D)
Rand_Index_3D_LowNoise_Spectral,cluster_LowNoise_Spectral=spectral_clustering(.5,3,centers_3D)

# plotting ARI vs number of clusters for each level of noise separately for 2D data
def Plot(x,y,z,cluster,RandIndex,title):
    plt.subplot(x,y,z)
    data={'Number of Clusters':cluster,'ARI':RandIndex}
    sns.lineplot(x='Number of Clusters',y='ARI',data=data)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Clusters')
    plt.ylabel('ARI')
    plt.title(title)
    maxid = np.argmax(RandIndex) # The id of the peak (maximum of Rand_Index-2D)
    print('The maximum value for ARI is '+str(RandIndex[maxid])+ ' and the number of clusters corresponding to this is '+str(cluster[maxid]))


f, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 15), sharex=True)
f.suptitle('Plotting ARI vs Number of Clusters for Each Level of Noise for 2D Data')
